# 088-network-layer — CoreDNS resolves the chain's internal service names.
#
# The backend's `dns:` points here (docker-compose), so service-name lookups the
# chain makes (e.g. "backend", "kong") are genuinely resolved by CoreDNS, with a
# TTL. Docker's own embedded DNS (127.0.0.11) is the upstream for the compose
# network's service names; everything else forwards to a public resolver.
#
# This makes DNS a real, separately-deployed hop — not just Docker's implicit
# resolver. Honest caveat (§3): the *browser* still uses the host's resolver;
# CoreDNS resolves the chain's internal hops, not the end user's lookup.

. {
    # Resolve compose service names via Docker's embedded DNS, the rest publicly.
    forward . 127.0.0.11 1.1.1.1 {
        policy sequential
    }
    cache 30
    log
    errors
}
